---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About Fluly - Learn Languages the Natural Way">
  <main class="about-container">

    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="about-hero">
      <div class="container">
        <span class="hero-badge">Our Story</span>
        <h1>Built for the moment Duolingo stops working</h1>
        <p class="lead">
          Duolingo is great for the basics. But once you have the foundations, 
          it starts to feel slow - because it teaches sentences that are correct, 
          just not useful. Fluly exists to fix that.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Founder -->
    <section class="founder-section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="founder-card">
          <div class="founder-avatar">EM</div>
          <div class="founder-text">
            <p class="founder-quote">
              "I wanted to learn a language the way native speakers actually use it - 
              not from a textbook, but from movies, books, games, and real conversations. 
              I couldn't find an app that did that well, so I built one."
            </p>
            <p class="founder-name">Emmanuel Mambwe — Founder, Fluly</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- The Problem -->
    <section class="problem-section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="two-col">
          <div class="two-col__text">
            <span class="section-label">The Problem</span>
            <h2>Most apps teach language. Fluly teaches you to use it.</h2>
            <p>
              Traditional language apps, including Duolingo - rely on pre-made lessons 
              with artificial sentences. "The elephant drinks water." Correct grammar. 
              Useless in real life.
            </p>
            <p>
              Real fluency comes from consuming the language the way native speakers do. 
              From films, books, podcasts, and conversations - not multiple choice questions.
            </p>
          <p>
  Fluly is built around the <strong>Birkenbihl method</strong> - understand 
  language in context, decode it word by word, listen passively, and let 
  fluency emerge naturally. No vocabulary lists. No drilling.
</p>
<p>
  Think about how you learned your first language. No child sits down with 
  flashcards. They are surrounded by the language - hearing it, seeing it 
  used in real situations - and they just pick it up. Exposure, not effort, 
  is what builds fluency.
</p>
<p>
  Fluly works the same way. Real movies. Real books.  Real podcasts. Real 
  conversations. Real games, yes we have games. That is the core - not artificial lessons written by an algorithm.
</p>

<div class="ai-clarity">
  <p class="ai-clarity__heading">On AI - we want to be clear:</p>
  <p>
    Fluly does not use AI to generate your learning content. What you learn 
    from is real, human-created material that native speakers actually consume.
  </p>
  <p>AI only comes in when <em>you</em> ask for it:</p>
  <ul class="ai-clarity__list">
    <li>Want a word explained in context? AI can do that.</li>
    <li>Want to generate your own custom lesson? AI can help.</li>
    <li>Want practice sentences based on content you have already studied? AI builds those for you.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    AI is a tool in Fluly - not the foundation. The foundation is real 
    language, used by real people.
  </p>
</div>
          </div>
          <div class="two-col__visual">
            <div class="comparison-card">
              <div class="comparison-col comparison-col--bad">
                <p class="comparison-label">Traditional apps</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>❌ Pre-made textbook sentences</li>
                  <li>❌ Tap the correct answer</li>
                  <li>❌ Generic content for everyone</li>
                  <li>❌ Slow after the basics</li>
                  <li>❌ Gamification over real fluency</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="comparison-col comparison-col--good">
                <p class="comparison-label">Fluly</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>✅ Content native speakers actually use</li>
                  <li>✅ Immersion-based learning</li>
                  <li>✅ Your interests drive your lessons</li>
                  <li>✅ Scales with your level</li>
                  <li>✅ Real fluency, measurable progress</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- How It Works -->
    <section class="method-section">
      <div class="container">
        <span class="section-label">The Method</span>
        <h2>The Birkenbihl Method - Context Theory</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">
          Dr. Vera F. Birkenbihl spent decades studying how the brain naturally acquires 
          language, e.i in context, effortless and understanding . When you understand it you learn it. Fluly brings that research to your phone.
        </p>
         <h2>Dr. Steven Krashen - Comprehensible Input Theory</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">
         Dr. Stephen Krashen's research shows we acquire language best when 
  we understand messages slightly beyond our current level - not by studying rules 
  or memorizing words. 
        </p>
        <p>Fluly brings both theories together in one app.</p>
        <div class="method-steps">
          <div class="method-step">
            <div class="step-number">01</div>
            <h3>Decode</h3>
            <p>Read a word-for-word translation alongside the original text. Your brain maps meaning without translation - the way children learn.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="method-step">
            <div class="step-number">02</div>
            <h3>Listen</h3>
            <p>Passive listening while you understand the content. Your brain absorbs pronunciation and rhythm without conscious effort.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="method-step">
            <div class="step-number">03</div>
            <h3>Activate</h3>
            <p>Interactive reading, speech dictation, and AI-generated practice - all based on the content you actually care about.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="method-step">
            <div class="step-number">04</div>
            <h3>Retain</h3>
            <p>Streaks, XP, and spaced repetition built around your real usage - not arbitrary tap-the-answer games.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Features -->
    <section class="features-section">
      <div class="container">
        <span class="section-label">What's Inside</span>
        <h2>Everything built around real language</h2>
        <div class="features-grid">
          <div class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon">🤖</div>
            <h3>AI-Generated Content(Optional)</h3>
            <p>If you want personalized practice materials, Fluly's AI can generate content tailored to your interests and learning style.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon">📖</div>
            <h3>Word-by-Word Translation</h3>
            <p>See exactly how the language maps to your native tongue. No guessing. No confusion.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon">📚</div>
            <h3>EPUB Book Learning</h3>
            <p>Import any eBook and learn from literature you actually want to read.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon">🎧</div>
            <h3>Passive Listening Mode</h3>
            <p>Keep learning while you commute, cook, or exercise. Your brain works even when you're not focused.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon">🗣️</div>
            <h3>Speech Dictation</h3>
            <p>Practice speaking and get real-time feedback. Pronunciation matters.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon">🔊</div>
            <h3>Pronunciation Audio</h3>
            <p>Hear every word spoken naturally. Not a robot - natural, native-like speech.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon">⚡</div>
            <h3>Streaks & XP</h3>
            <p>Progress systems that reward real learning - not just showing up and tapping answers.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon">🌍</div>
            <h3>304+ Languages</h3>
            <p>Including 80+ African languages that most apps completely ignore.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Mascot -->
    <section class="mascot-section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="mascot-content">
          <div class="mascot-svg" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg width="200" viewBox="0 0 680 500" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
              <ellipse cx="340" cy="418" rx="105" ry="15" fill="#7C3AED" opacity="0.14"/>
              <path d="M 340 160 C 395 152 458 182 466 238 C 474 294 458 355 418 383 C 390 403 350 410 308 400 C 262 388 222 354 214 300 C 206 246 228 192 278 168 C 300 157 322 163 340 160 Z" fill="#7C3AED"/>
              <ellipse cx="374" cy="207" rx="50" ry="32" fill="#9F67F0" opacity="0.38" transform="rotate(-18 374 207)"/>
              <circle cx="305" cy="268" r="26" fill="white"/>
              <circle cx="308" cy="272" r="15" fill="#1a0533"/>
              <circle cx="301" cy="264" r="5.5" fill="white"/>
              <circle cx="376" cy="268" r="26" fill="white"/>
              <circle cx="379" cy="272" r="15" fill="#1a0533"/>
              <circle cx="372" cy="264" r="5.5" fill="white"/>
              <path d="M 312 318 Q 341 342 370 318" stroke="white" stroke-width="3.5" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              <ellipse cx="284" cy="302" rx="17" ry="10" fill="#F9A8D4" opacity="0.48"/>
              <ellipse cx="396" cy="302" rx="17" ry="10" fill="#F9A8D4" opacity="0.48"/>
              <path d="M 198 268 Q 191 283 198 298" stroke="#A78BFA" stroke-width="2.5" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              <path d="M 184 256 Q 174 283 184 310" stroke="#A78BFA" stroke-width="2" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0.7"/>
              <path d="M 170 244 Q 157 283 170 322" stroke="#A78BFA" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0.45"/>
              <path d="M 482 268 Q 489 283 482 298" stroke="#A78BFA" stroke-width="2.5" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              <path d="M 496 256 Q 506 283 496 310" stroke="#A78BFA" stroke-width="2" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0.7"/>
              <path d="M 510 244 Q 523 283 510 322" stroke="#A78BFA" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0.45"/>
              <rect x="291" y="428" width="98" height="32" rx="16" fill="#7C3AED" opacity="0.88"/>
              <text x="340" y="449" text-anchor="middle" fill="white" font-size="13" font-weight="500">Ciao! 👋</text>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="mascot-text">
            <span class="section-label">Meet Plum</span>
            <h2>The face of natural learning</h2>
            <p>
              Plum is Fluly's mascot - a friendly blob who represents what language 
              learning should feel like. Approachable, curious, and always happy to help 
              you find the right word.
            </p>
            <p>
              Like a plum tree, fluency takes root slowly and quietly -
              then one day you realise you're just speaking.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Download -->
    <section class="about-cta">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Ready to learn the natural way?</h2>
        <p class="cta-subtitle">
          Available on iOS. Android APK available on GitHub.
        </p>
        <div class="cta-buttons">
          <a href="#" class="btn btn-accent">Download on App Store</a>
          <a href="https://github.com" class="btn btn-outline">Get APK on GitHub</a>
        </div>
        <p class="cta-note">Free to download. No credit card required.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
    .ai-clarity {
  margin-top: 2rem;
  padding: 1.5rem;
  background: rgba(91, 82, 240, 0.06);
  border: 1px solid rgba(91, 82, 240, 0.18);
  border-radius: 14px;
}

.ai-clarity__heading {
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--color-highlight-purple, #A89DFF);
  margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
}

.ai-clarity__list {
  padding-left: 1.25rem;
  margin: 0.75rem 0;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 0.5rem;
}

.ai-clarity__list li {
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  color: #94A3B8;
  line-height: 1.6;
}
